1
00:00:38,820 --> 00:00:40,820
=Visage and Soul=

2
00:00:40,820 --> 00:00:43,040
(The "Different Her"
Trilogy on Women's Relationships)

3
00:00:44,720 --> 00:00:47,640
=Episode 12=

4
00:00:49,640 --> 00:00:51,120
Just a reminder. Don't get too
caught up in your act.

5
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:54,480
You'd better not do anything reckless.

6
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:56,320
If something goes wrong,

7
00:00:56,320 --> 00:00:57,440
it'll be too late for regrets.

8
00:01:07,520 --> 00:01:08,120
Bye.

9
00:01:08,320 --> 00:01:09,640
Bye.

10
00:01:19,880 --> 00:01:21,520
Thanks for coming with me today.

11
00:01:21,520 --> 00:01:22,520
I got you a coffee.

12
00:01:23,840 --> 00:01:25,320
How did you know caramel's my favorite?

13
00:01:26,360 --> 00:01:27,400
I lost my memory.

14
00:01:27,400 --> 00:01:28,240
I didn't lose my eyesight.

15
00:01:28,240 --> 00:01:29,400
You drink this every day.

16
00:01:35,160 --> 00:01:36,400
I'm so nervous.

17
00:01:37,520 --> 00:01:38,520
It's my first time
organizing an exhibition.

18
00:01:38,520 --> 00:01:39,800
What if I mess everything up

19
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:41,640
and embarrass my dad?

20
00:01:46,240 --> 00:01:47,040
You've got me.

21
00:01:52,760 --> 00:01:53,600
Thank you.

22
00:01:55,400 --> 00:01:56,440
Happy to help.

23
00:02:09,960 --> 00:02:11,120
Did you hear?

24
00:02:11,120 --> 00:02:12,880
Someone saw this painting

25
00:02:12,880 --> 00:02:13,880
at a private auction in
Hong Kong, China last night.

26
00:02:14,320 --> 00:02:15,120
What do you mean?

27
00:02:15,600 --> 00:02:17,840
Are you blind? There's
something wrong with this painting.

28
00:02:18,080 --> 00:02:19,000
What?

29
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:20,560
Are you saying it's a fake?

30
00:02:20,800 --> 00:02:22,360
What are you two whispering about?

31
00:02:22,360 --> 00:02:24,320
If you've got something
to say, just say it.

32
00:02:24,320 --> 00:02:26,680
We suspect this painting is a forgery.

33
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:28,120
How could it possibly be fake?

34
00:02:28,120 --> 00:02:29,320
It's my father's final work.

35
00:02:31,200 --> 00:02:32,880
Are you questioning this painting,

36
00:02:32,880 --> 00:02:34,520
or are you questioning
my sister, Qiao Xiaomi?

37
00:02:34,800 --> 00:02:35,680
That's right.

38
00:02:35,680 --> 00:02:37,080
Xiaomi may have lost her memory.

39
00:02:37,080 --> 00:02:38,200
She may not know how to run a company.

40
00:02:38,800 --> 00:02:40,440
She may not even know
how to paint anymore.

41
00:02:40,840 --> 00:02:41,960
But she is still

42
00:02:41,960 --> 00:02:43,480
the sole legal heir of the Qiao family.

43
00:02:44,080 --> 00:02:46,400
She was the daughter
my father loved the most.

44
00:02:46,400 --> 00:02:47,560
And she's also

45
00:02:47,560 --> 00:02:49,440
the last family member
I have in this world.

46
00:02:49,760 --> 00:02:51,800
I won't allow anyone to slander her.

47
00:02:52,200 --> 00:02:53,920
Qiao Zhiwei, what are you playing at?

48
00:02:54,400 --> 00:02:55,040
Xiaomi.

49
00:02:55,600 --> 00:02:57,200
I won't let anyone bully you.

50
00:03:04,800 --> 00:03:05,240
What...

51
00:03:07,720 --> 00:03:09,080
What is he doing?

52
00:03:10,080 --> 00:03:11,120
Everyone, please remain calm.

53
00:03:11,680 --> 00:03:13,360
This isn't a deception.

54
00:03:13,360 --> 00:03:15,000
It's actually

55
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:16,920
a specially designed

56
00:03:16,920 --> 00:03:18,360
opening event for this exhibition.

57
00:03:19,080 --> 00:03:20,560
Mindscapes and Illusions.

58
00:03:21,080 --> 00:03:23,360
A public session on healing through art.

59
00:03:24,040 --> 00:03:24,720
And now,

60
00:03:24,880 --> 00:03:26,400
please welcome our Doctor of Psychology,

61
00:03:26,400 --> 00:03:27,360
Dr. Chen Yue.

62
00:03:35,280 --> 00:03:36,520
The painting was switched.

63
00:03:36,520 --> 00:03:38,320
What can a psychologist do here?

64
00:03:38,520 --> 00:03:39,440
Art therapy.

65
00:03:39,640 --> 00:03:40,440
Dr. Chen.

66
00:03:40,800 --> 00:03:42,320
What if we turn this to our advantage?

67
00:03:42,320 --> 00:03:43,640
Instead of treating
the fake painting as a scandal,

68
00:03:43,840 --> 00:03:46,120
we make it part of the
art therapy experience.

69
00:03:48,840 --> 00:03:50,000
What do you mean by that?

70
00:03:51,440 --> 00:03:53,160
In a moment, we'll announce

71
00:03:53,160 --> 00:03:55,440
that this exhibition features
a special opening event.

72
00:03:56,240 --> 00:03:57,720
Mindscapes and Illusions.

73
00:03:57,920 --> 00:04:00,600
A public session on healing through art.

74
00:04:01,640 --> 00:04:02,920
Why are you doing this?

75
00:04:04,640 --> 00:04:06,320
I'm Xiaomi's fiancé.

76
00:04:06,320 --> 00:04:07,400
I have to protect her.

77
00:04:09,320 --> 00:04:10,240
This really is

78
00:04:10,240 --> 00:04:12,320
a great opportunity to
promote art therapy.

79
00:04:12,680 --> 00:04:13,560
It's just that...

80
00:04:13,920 --> 00:04:15,160
the fake painting's
going to be destroyed.

81
00:04:15,440 --> 00:04:16,280
Where's the real one?

82
00:04:18,920 --> 00:04:19,720
Leave that to me.

83
00:04:20,320 --> 00:04:21,320
By the way, Dr. Chen.

84
00:04:21,600 --> 00:04:22,960
I hope you won't tell Xiaomi

85
00:04:22,960 --> 00:04:24,000
about any of this.

86
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:25,240
I need her to be completely safe.

87
00:04:28,240 --> 00:04:28,800
Alright.

88
00:04:32,040 --> 00:04:33,520
Psychological healing?

89
00:04:34,440 --> 00:04:35,840
That sounds fascinating.

90
00:04:35,840 --> 00:04:37,400
This damaged painting

91
00:04:37,400 --> 00:04:39,240
symbolizes false memories,

92
00:04:39,240 --> 00:04:41,200
trauma masks, and cognitive barriers

93
00:04:41,200 --> 00:04:43,400
that may exist deep within each of us.

94
00:04:44,120 --> 00:04:45,280
Breaking them apart

95
00:04:45,600 --> 00:04:47,280
is the first step toward healing.

96
00:04:47,440 --> 00:04:48,680
Facing trauma.

97
00:04:49,280 --> 00:04:50,320
Letting go of obsessions.

98
00:04:50,520 --> 00:04:52,440
Using this damaged painting
as inspiration,

99
00:04:52,440 --> 00:04:53,280
we'll explore

100
00:04:53,840 --> 00:04:55,120
how art becomes part of life

101
00:04:55,440 --> 00:04:56,920
and helps heal the human spirit.

102
00:04:56,920 --> 00:04:57,720
Later,

103
00:04:58,320 --> 00:04:59,480
the authentic version of this painting

104
00:04:59,760 --> 00:05:02,480
will be exhibited free
of charge for everyone.

105
00:05:02,720 --> 00:05:04,560
Anyone who's interested
is welcome to step forward.

106
00:05:05,880 --> 00:05:07,760
This is far more than
a simple fake painting.

107
00:05:19,200 --> 00:05:19,960
Zhiwei,

108
00:05:20,200 --> 00:05:22,320
I honestly had no idea
what Qin Yu was up to.

109
00:05:22,320 --> 00:05:23,120
If I knew,

110
00:05:23,120 --> 00:05:24,320
I would've told you beforehand.

111
00:05:24,320 --> 00:05:25,240
That's enough.

112
00:05:25,840 --> 00:05:27,920
Qin Yu may have acted
on his own this time,

113
00:05:27,920 --> 00:05:29,040
but at least things

114
00:05:29,040 --> 00:05:30,520
are moving in the direction I wanted.

115
00:05:34,240 --> 00:05:35,520
I'll be honest with you.

116
00:05:35,960 --> 00:05:37,000
Qin Yu works for me.

117
00:05:37,360 --> 00:05:38,600
He works for you?

118
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:41,520
But he spent the whole day
helping Qiao Xiaomi.

119
00:05:41,520 --> 00:05:42,920
It's called acting.

120
00:05:43,680 --> 00:05:44,440
If he doesn't make it look real,

121
00:05:44,440 --> 00:05:45,840
how's he supposed to earn her trust?

122
00:05:50,120 --> 00:05:51,320
I see.

123
00:05:52,880 --> 00:05:53,600
Zhiwei,

124
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:56,240
it's not that I'm questioning your plan.

125
00:05:56,720 --> 00:05:57,560
It's just that...

126
00:05:57,560 --> 00:05:58,400
don't you think

127
00:05:58,400 --> 00:06:00,120
he went a little too far today?

128
00:06:00,320 --> 00:06:02,480
Is he really doing
exactly what you told him to do?

129
00:06:02,760 --> 00:06:03,920
Today,

130
00:06:03,920 --> 00:06:05,520
he and that psychologist

131
00:06:05,520 --> 00:06:06,440
stole all the spotlight.

132
00:06:06,760 --> 00:06:08,240
It actually made you
look a bit sidelined.

133
00:06:09,160 --> 00:06:11,080
So tell me, is he helping you,

134
00:06:11,080 --> 00:06:14,040
or is he using your setup
to advance his own agenda?

135
00:06:16,280 --> 00:06:17,320
Besides,

136
00:06:17,320 --> 00:06:20,000
Qiao Xiaomi depends on him so much now.
She trusts him completely.

137
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:21,800
She's lost her memory
and is so easy to fool.

138
00:06:22,680 --> 00:06:25,080
What if he starts
taking the act seriously

139
00:06:25,080 --> 00:06:26,400
and develops other intentions?

140
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:29,280
Then he'll end up
benefiting from both sides.

141
00:06:29,280 --> 00:06:30,160
And we'll just...

142
00:06:30,160 --> 00:06:31,120
He wouldn't dare.

143
00:07:17,640 --> 00:07:19,960
Where have you been
these past three years?

144
00:07:24,320 --> 00:07:26,560
Why did you only come back now?

145
00:07:28,600 --> 00:07:30,680
These past three years,

146
00:07:32,080 --> 00:07:33,960
I've had such a hard time on my own.

147
00:07:49,800 --> 00:07:51,240
Did you get home?

148
00:07:52,240 --> 00:07:52,960
Worried about me?

149
00:07:52,960 --> 00:07:54,320
Who said I was worried about you?

150
00:07:54,320 --> 00:07:55,720
I was just checking

151
00:07:55,720 --> 00:07:57,200
that you didn't pass out
drunk by the roadside.

152
00:07:57,200 --> 00:07:59,880
Is it really that hard
to admit you're worried about me?

153
00:08:00,400 --> 00:08:01,800
I'm heading to bed. Good night.

154
00:08:04,200 --> 00:08:07,240
♪Let's love each day♪

155
00:08:07,760 --> 00:08:12,040
♪as if it were our last♪

156
00:08:12,960 --> 00:08:16,400
♪Every second, every moment♪

157
00:08:17,400 --> 00:08:18,440
You're here.

158
00:08:19,280 --> 00:08:20,400
Come in.

159
00:08:29,400 --> 00:08:30,640
I've been waiting for you.

160
00:08:35,320 --> 00:08:36,920
I went to have dinner with her.

161
00:08:38,320 --> 00:08:39,440
Looks like you had a good time.

162
00:08:41,120 --> 00:08:43,200
She's becoming
more and more dependent on me now.

163
00:08:43,480 --> 00:08:44,800
And she trusts me even more.

164
00:08:46,280 --> 00:08:48,160
I'd say you're getting
a little too invested in the role.

165
00:08:50,040 --> 00:08:51,880
I'm just making sure nothing goes wrong.

166
00:08:53,400 --> 00:08:54,960
Nothing goes wrong?

167
00:08:58,200 --> 00:08:59,880
Don't forget who you are.

168
00:09:02,800 --> 00:09:03,520
Zhiwei.

169
00:09:04,080 --> 00:09:05,240
I've brought him here.

170
00:09:06,600 --> 00:09:08,120
Mr. Qiao, I've heard so much about you.

171
00:09:08,120 --> 00:09:09,920
Mr. Luo said you had a project
you wanted to discuss with me.

172
00:09:21,840 --> 00:09:22,760
Wow.

173
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:26,960
You look so much alike.

174
00:09:30,080 --> 00:09:30,760
This...

175
00:09:31,040 --> 00:09:32,720
This is practically me.

176
00:09:33,760 --> 00:09:34,640
I heard

177
00:09:35,040 --> 00:09:37,000
your father left behind
a mountain of debt

178
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:37,880
and skipped town.

179
00:09:37,880 --> 00:09:39,600
Now the debt collectors
are coming after you.

180
00:09:40,240 --> 00:09:40,960
That's right.

181
00:09:42,240 --> 00:09:43,000
Mr. Qiao,

182
00:09:43,320 --> 00:09:44,400
how did you know that?

183
00:09:44,400 --> 00:09:45,240
That's not your concern.

184
00:09:45,800 --> 00:09:47,120
Do you want to put this
whole thing behind you?

185
00:09:47,520 --> 00:09:48,240
Of course I do.

186
00:09:49,480 --> 00:09:50,640
You have a way to help me?

187
00:09:50,640 --> 00:09:51,440
Of course.

188
00:09:51,880 --> 00:09:53,680
I have a role I'd like you to play.

189
00:09:53,680 --> 00:09:55,320
The question is
whether you're interested.

190
00:09:56,520 --> 00:09:59,120
It all depends on

191
00:09:59,120 --> 00:10:00,480
whether you're willing to take the role

192
00:10:00,880 --> 00:10:02,280
and whether you can pull it off.

193
00:10:03,600 --> 00:10:05,160
I can definitely pull it off.

194
00:10:05,680 --> 00:10:06,280
But...

195
00:10:06,760 --> 00:10:07,360
what's

196
00:10:07,360 --> 00:10:08,520
the story?

197
00:10:08,520 --> 00:10:09,520
Is there a script?

198
00:10:09,960 --> 00:10:10,560
I...

199
00:10:10,560 --> 00:10:11,920
Don't worry about the script.

200
00:10:11,920 --> 00:10:13,920
I guarantee it'll be a great one.

201
00:10:13,920 --> 00:10:15,040
Starting now,

202
00:10:18,040 --> 00:10:19,600
you're my leading man.

203
00:10:24,600 --> 00:10:26,480
You're just a nobody actor,

204
00:10:26,640 --> 00:10:28,040
yet you came up
with an idea like art therapy

205
00:10:28,040 --> 00:10:29,920
to help Qiao Xiaomi.

206
00:10:30,760 --> 00:10:31,760
I'm impressed.

207
00:10:34,400 --> 00:10:35,200
Mr. Qiao,

208
00:10:36,720 --> 00:10:38,120
with your eye for talent,

209
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:40,240
how could you possibly
pick the wrong person?

210
00:10:42,520 --> 00:10:43,680
Cut the flattery.

211
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:46,200
Let me make this clear.

212
00:10:46,840 --> 00:10:48,760
The original two-month deadline
is canceled.

213
00:10:48,760 --> 00:10:50,000
If by this time next month

214
00:10:50,560 --> 00:10:52,160
I still haven't seen Qiao Xiaomi

215
00:10:52,160 --> 00:10:54,160
sign the stock transfer agreement,

216
00:10:56,920 --> 00:10:58,280
don't blame me for turning against you.

217
00:10:59,520 --> 00:11:00,520
Deal.

218
00:11:04,800 --> 00:11:07,120
Don't tell me you've actually
fallen for Xiaomi.

219
00:11:52,764 --> 00:11:54,834
♪We say good morning, we say good night♪

220
00:11:54,834 --> 00:11:58,254
♪We say we miss each other,
but never speak of the hurt♪

221
00:11:59,854 --> 00:12:01,744
♪The sweeter it is, the luckier we seem♪

222
00:12:01,744 --> 00:12:05,734
♪Yet the more romantic,
the rougher the road♪

223
00:12:06,974 --> 00:12:08,834
♪Let me go, set me free♪

224
00:12:08,834 --> 00:12:12,874
♪Let me drown in reckless silence♪

225
00:12:13,414 --> 00:12:18,824
♪We were perfect for each other,
yet you never admitted it♪

226
00:12:20,174 --> 00:12:22,314
♪The freedom you gave me♪

227
00:12:22,314 --> 00:12:25,954
♪Became the heaviest chain I bear♪

228
00:12:27,214 --> 00:12:29,484
♪Love can barely move forward♪

229
00:12:29,484 --> 00:12:33,264
♪Yet the words still linger unspoken♪

230
00:12:34,364 --> 00:12:36,604
♪The closeness I long for♪

231
00:12:36,604 --> 00:12:40,994
♪There's no need for you
to keep avoiding it♪

232
00:12:41,404 --> 00:12:43,224
♪I don't want to break free♪

233
00:12:43,224 --> 00:12:48,594
♪Take back the chains
disguised as freedom♪
